Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force November 1
In parallel to its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the Congressional vote on the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim of both coming into force before the end of the year.
Representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and consensualize the best regulations in order to ensure the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Markets Act, involves the modernization of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new rules will allow the provision of financial advisory services to specialized firms as well as to natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory firms (AFIs), which join stock companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of trades in financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are added to the multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with the current stock exchange managers.
The law also requires investment services firms to disclose in the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management forms and requires them to keep a record of all the operations they carry out, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Congressional Economic Commission, several modifications were incorporated, among which it highlights that the securitised debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of US high-risk mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can perform 30 years after the adoption in 1977 of the royal decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work on behalf of others, will not require authorization from the CNMV and will be able to provide its services of product marketing and customer acquisition to different investment companies at the same time.
