NHS hopes to carry out pre-employment checks on candidates, to ensure they meet the qualifications, experience and authorization to work in the UK.
Although the Scottish health board uses “Disclosure Scotland” to conduct criminal background checks, the agency has no jurisdiction to obtain this information outside of Britain.
The auditor general’s report recommends, among other measures, that the boards should have the guidance of the Criminal Records Bureau, which helps employers with criminal controls in many countries outside of Britain.
“Although we found some of the personal records with evidence of these controls, this is not a routine review,” the report says.
